article.headline: Kent State 81, IPFW 72
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Scott Cutley scored 22 points and Kent State made free throws when it mattered, holding off hot-shooting Indiana-Purdue-Fort Wayne 81-72 Monday night. The Mastodons (4-14) shot 55.1 percent from the field and made 13 of 27 from 3-point range, including three to trim a 75-61 deficit to 75-70 with 35 seconds remaining. The Golden Flashes (11-6) hit six free throws to seal the win and finished 29-for-34 at the foul line. Indiana-Purdue-Fort Wayne attempted just six free throws, making five. Cutley went 8-for-9 from the field and 5-for-7 at the line. DeAndre Haynes was 8-of-9 at the line and had 16 points, five assists and five steals for the Golden Flashes. Jason Edwin and Armon Gates each scored 13 for Kent State. Peter Campbell led the Mastodons with 28 points and 10 rebounds while making seven of his 13 3-point shots, two in the late 9-0 run that made it a five-point game. Beau Bauer added 13 points and David Simon and Quintin Carouthers each had 10 for the Mastodons.
